---
dops: v1
kind: tool

meta:
  name: nginx
  version: 1.0.0
  description: "Generate Nginx reverse proxy and server configurations"
  author: dojops
  license: MIT
  tags: [nginx, proxy, reverse-proxy, web-server, load-balancer]

input:
  fields:
    serverName:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Server name / domain (e.g. 'example.com')"
    upstreams:
      type: string
      description: "Upstream backend servers description"
    sslEnabled:
      type: boolean
      default: false
    outputPath:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Directory to write the config to"
    fullConfig:
      type: boolean
      default: false
      description: "Generate a full nginx.conf instead of a site config"
    environment:
      type: string

output:
  type: object
  required: [content]
  properties:
    content:
      type: string
      description: "Complete Nginx configuration as text"

files:
  - path: "{outputPath}/nginx.conf"
    format: raw
    source: llm
    dataPath: content

detection:
  paths: ["nginx.conf", "nginx/*.conf", "conf.d/*.conf", "sites-available/*"]
  updateMode: true

verification:
  structural:
    - path: "content"
      required: true
      type: string
      message: "Nginx configuration content is required"

  binary:
    command: "nginx -t -c nginx.conf"
    parser: nginx-stderr
    timeout: 30000
    cwd: output

permissions:
  filesystem: write
  child_process: required
  network: none

scope:
  write: ["{outputPath}/nginx.conf"]

risk:
  level: MEDIUM
  rationale: "Web server config changes affect traffic routing"

execution:
  mode: generate
  deterministic: false
  idempotent: true

update:
  strategy: replace
  inputSource: file
  injectAs: existingContent
---
# Nginx

## Prompt

You are an Nginx expert. Generate an Nginx configuration as text.

You MUST respond with a JSON object containing a "content" field with the complete Nginx configuration as a string.

The configuration should include:
- Upstream blocks for backend servers (if applicable)
- Server blocks with proper listen directives
- Location blocks for routing
- SSL configuration if enabled
- Security headers
- Logging configuration

Response format:
{
  "content": "upstream backend {\n    server 127.0.0.1:3000;\n}\n\nserver {\n    listen 80;\n    server_name example.com;\n\n    location / {\n        proxy_pass http://backend;\n        proxy_set_header Host $host;\n        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\n    }\n}\n"
}

IMPORTANT:
- "content" must contain the COMPLETE Nginx configuration as a string
- Include proper proxy headers for reverse proxy setups
- Use proper indentation (4 spaces)
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Update Prompt

You are an Nginx expert. Update the existing Nginx configuration.
Preserve existing server blocks and settings. Only add/modify what is requested.

--- EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---
{existingContent}
--- END EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---

Respond with a JSON object containing a "content" field with the complete updated Nginx config.

IMPORTANT:
- Preserve ALL existing server blocks unless explicitly asked to remove them
- Maintain existing upstream and location configurations
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Examples

Given: "Reverse proxy for Node.js app on port 3000 with SSL"

```json
{
  "content": "upstream app_backend {\n    server 127.0.0.1:3000;\n    keepalive 32;\n}\n\nserver {\n    listen 80;\n    server_name example.com;\n    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;\n}\n\nserver {\n    listen 443 ssl http2;\n    server_name example.com;\n\n    ssl_certificate /etc/ssl/certs/example.com.pem;\n    ssl_certificate_key /etc/ssl/private/example.com.key;\n    ssl_protocols TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3;\n    ssl_ciphers HIGH:!aNULL:!MD5;\n\n    add_header X-Frame-Options DENY;\n    add_header X-Content-Type-Options nosniff;\n    add_header X-XSS-Protection \"1; mode=block\";\n\n    location / {\n        proxy_pass http://app_backend;\n        proxy_set_header Host $host;\n        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\n        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\n        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;\n    }\n}\n"
}
```

## Constraints

- Use HTTP/2 when SSL is enabled
- Include security headers (X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options)
- Set proper proxy headers for reverse proxy
- Use keepalive connections for upstreams
- Include access and error log paths
- No hardcoded IP addresses for production

## Keywords

nginx, reverse-proxy, proxy, web-server, load-balancer, server,
upstream, ssl, tls, https, location, conf, vhost, site
